cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the evolution of English language and word frequency, which falls under the domain of natural language processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of neutral models to replicate the emergent properties of the corpus data. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper deals with the evolution of cultural variants and their popularity over time. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is a possible category as the paper uses data from three centuries of English language books. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the impact of mass attention on a small subset of cultural variants.
